## 1. Astro 5.x Mental Model <a name="astro-mental-model"></a>

Astro is a **static-first** framework. The default behavior is to ship **zero JavaScript** to the browser. Components render to HTML at build time, and only the parts you explicitly mark as interactive ("islands") get hydrated with JavaScript.

### Core Principles

1. **Server-first**: Components run on the server by default. No JS shipped unless you opt in.
2. **Islands**: Interactive components are "islands" of JavaScript in a "sea" of static HTML.
3. **Framework-agnostic**: Use React, Vue, Svelte, or Solid — even mix them on the same page.
4. **Partial hydration**: Only load JS for the components that need it, when they need it.

### How It Differs from Next.js/Vite

| Feature | Astro | Next.js | Vite (React) |
|---------|-------|---------|-------------|
| Default JS | Zero | Full bundle | Full bundle |
| Rendering | Static HTML | SSR + Hydration | CSR |
| Interactivity | Opt-in (islands) | Opt-out (`use server`) | Always on |
| Routing | File-based | File-based | Manual (react-router) |
| Best for | Content sites, portfolios | Web apps | SPAs |

### File Structure

```
portfolio/
├── public/               # Static assets (served as-is)
│   ├── fonts/
│   └── images/
├── src/
│   ├── components/       # Reusable components
│   │   ├── LaptopShell.astro    # Static shell (no JS)
│   │   └── Terminal.tsx          # Interactive island (React)
│   ├── layouts/
│   │   └── Layout.astro         # Base HTML layout
│   ├── pages/
│   │   └── index.astro          # Routes (file = URL)
│   └── styles/
│       ├── global.css           # Design tokens + resets
│       ├── laptop.css           # ThinkPad styling
│       ├── terminal.css         # Terminal emulator
│       └── crt.css              # CRT scanline effects
├── astro.config.mjs
├── package.json
└── tsconfig.json
```

---

## 2. Islands Architecture & Partial Hydration <a name="islands-architecture"></a>

### The Island Concept

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    Page (Static HTML)                  │
│                                                        │
│  ┌──────────────┐   ┌──────────────────────────────┐  │
│  │   Header     │   │                              │  │
│  │  (Static)    │   │     Terminal Component       │  │
│  │  No JS ✨    │   │     (React Island)           │  │
│  └──────────────┘   │     JS loaded ⚡             │  │
│                      │                              │  │
│  ┌──────────────┐   │     - xterm.js               │  │
│  │   About      │   │     - Command handling       │  │
│  │  (Static)    │   │     - Keyboard events        │  │
│  │  No JS ✨    │   │                              │  │
│  └──────────────┘   └──────────────────────────────┘  │
│                                                        │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
│  │              Footer (Static) — No JS ✨           │  │
│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Only the Terminal component ships JavaScript. Everything else is pure HTML/CSS.

### Hydration Directives

Astro provides several directives to control *when* an island's JavaScript loads:

| Directive | When JS Loads | Use Case |
|-----------|--------------|----------|
| `client:load` | Immediately on page load | Critical interactive elements |
| `client:idle` | When browser is idle | Non-critical widgets |
| `client:visible` | When element scrolls into view | Below-fold components |
| `client:media="(max-width: 768px)"` | When media query matches | Mobile-only interactivity |
| `client:only="react"` | Client-only (no SSR) | Components using browser APIs |

```astro
---
// src/pages/index.astro
import Terminal from '../components/Terminal.tsx';
import Analytics from '../components/Analytics.tsx';
import MobileMenu from '../components/MobileMenu.tsx';
---

<!-- Loads JS immediately — terminal must work on page load -->
<Terminal client:load />

<!-- Loads JS when browser is idle — not critical -->
<Analytics client:idle />

<!-- Only loads on mobile viewports -->
<MobileMenu client:media="(max-width: 768px)" />
```

